    en: "A backyard trampoline is fun — and one of the biggest personal-injury risks on a residential property. New York's attractive nuisance doctrine lets a neighbor's family sue the homeowner when a child gets hurt on the trampoline, even when the child entered without permission. Many homeowner's insurance policies exclude trampolines, require a rider, or require specific safety features (net, fence, ground anchors) for coverage. The combination of common-law premises liability and insurance contract law drives the analysis."
